  "raw_meta_yaml": "context:\n  version: \"2.1.1\"\n  pkg_name: \"spotify-voyager\"\n\npackage:\n  name: ${{ pkg_name }}\n  version: ${{ version }}\n\nsource:\n  url: https://github.com/spotify/voyager/archive/refs/tags/v${{ version }}.tar.gz\n  sha256: b04306f63b3fdd7aada8ca2bd74d53ec6b0746623e6b69f3820c2c412c75a23e\n  # Fix broken Python metadata and replace the tarball's Unix-only src/cpp symlink.\n  patches:\n    - 0001-fix-python-package-metadata-and-includes.patch\n\nbuild:\n  number: 0\n  # Upstream's release workflow copies the repo-level C++ sources into\n  # python/src before building Python artifacts:\n  # https://github.com/spotify/voyager/blob/v2.1.1/.github/workflows/all.yml#L260-L264\n  # The v2.1.1 GitHub release tarball also carries broken Python package\n  # metadata; see https://github.com/spotify/voyager/pull/129.\n  script: build\n\nrequirements:\n  build:\n    - if: build_platform != target_platform\n      then:\n        - python\n        - cross-python_${{ target_platform }}\n        - numpy\n        - scikit-build-core\n        - nanobind\n        - cmake\n        - ninja\n    - ${{ compiler(\"cxx\") }}\n    - ${{ stdlib(\"c\") }}\n    - cmake\n    - ninja\n  host:\n    - python\n    - pip\n    - numpy\n    - scikit-build-core\n    - nanobind\n    - cmake\n    - ninja\n  run:\n    - python\n    - numpy\n\ntests:\n  - python:\n      imports:\n        - voyager\n      pip_check: true\n  - requirements:\n      run:\n        - numpy\n    script:\n      - python -c \"import numpy as np, voyager; x = np.array([[1.0, 0.0], [0.0, 1.0]], dtype=np.float32); index = voyager.Index(space=voyager.Space.Euclidean, num_dimensions=2); index.add_items(x); labels, distances = index.query(x[:1], k=1); assert int(labels[0, 0]) == 0; assert np.isclose(float(distances[0, 0]), 0.0)\"\n\nabout:\n  homepage: https://github.com/spotify/voyager\n  repository: https://github.com/spotify/voyager\n  summary: Approximate nearest-neighbor search library for Python and Java.\n  description: |\n    Voyager is an approximate nearest-neighbor search library from Spotify\n    with Python and Java bindings and a focus on ease of use, simplicity,\n    and deployability.\n  documentation: https://spotify.github.io/voyager/python\n  license: Apache-2.0\n  license_file: LICENSE\n\nextra:\n  feedstock_name: ${{ pkg_name }}\n  recipe-maintainers:\n    - moritzwilksch\n",
